Use Visual Studio (VS) Code and the Salesforce Extensions for CRM Analytics Template Development

Microsoft Visual Studio (VS) Code provides the fastest, most efficient way to work with CRM Analytics templates. Hereâ€™s how to install and set up the tool.

The VS Code Salesforce Analytics Extension Pack lets you work iteratively with templates using Salesforce DX (SFDX) and Salesforce CLI Analytics commands. Manage the lifecycle of a templated app from VS Code. Create a template from a CRM Analytics app. Edit the template JSON files to make the app customizable with a configuration wizard. Deploy the app to a scratch org to test it.

Install VS Code and Salesforce Extensions

Prerequisites: Install Salesforce CLI and the Analytics CLI plugin, and create a development org before you install Visual Studio (VS) Code.

Install VS Code, and get it set up for template development with the Salesforce Extension Pack and Salesforce Analytics Extension Pack.

Create a VS Code Project

Open VS Code, open the View menu, and select Command Palette. Type SFDX: Create Project with Manifest in the palette, and select SFDX: Create Project with Manifest from the options that appear.

Connect VS Code to Your Development Org

In VS Code, open the command palette again, type Auth, and select SFDX: Authorize an Org.

Issue Salesforce CLI commands for creating and managing Analytics templates from the VS Code Command Palette.
title: Setting Up Visual Studio Code for Salesforce CRM Analytics Template Development
